The President called King Salman bin Abdulaziz al-Saud of Saudi Arabia to discuss the political framework reached between the P5+1, the EU, and Iran on a Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action regarding Iran's nuclear program. They emphasized the need to finalize the technical details for a comprehensive solution that prevents Iran from obtaining a nuclear bomb. The President also expressed concerns about Iran's destabilizing activities in the region and reiterated that the nuclear understanding will not lessen U.S. concerns. They agreed to increase consultations and counter this threat. The President invited the King and Gulf Cooperation Council leaders to Camp David to continue discussions. They reaffirmed the enduring friendship between the United States and Saudi Arabia.